# Normalize line endings so a content pack's SHA-256 (ADR-000 D5.5) is
# identical on every platform. Without this, a Windows checkout with
# autocrlf=true rewrites text files to CRLF, changing their bytes and their
# hash, and the determinism/golden-replay job fails only on Windows.

# Default: treat everything Git detects as text as text, and always check it
# out with LF line endings regardless of core.autocrlf.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Belt-and-suspenders for the files whose exact bytes are hashed or replayed.
*.json  text eol=lf
*.go    text eol=lf
*.sh    text eol=lf
*.md    text eol=lf
*.yml   text eol=lf

# Binary assets (none today) must never be normalized; keep this line as the
# place to declare them.
*.png binary
